"title": "5865: gestures",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5865: gestures",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Significant acts, bodily movements or signals which carry meaning, evoke responses or convey positive or negative feelings.  They may or may not be accompanied by words or other communications.</p>\n<h2>Gestures are part of human communication</h2>\n<h3>They give weight to a contract</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:7\">RUT 4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:22-2Sam24:24\">2SA 24:22–24:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:23-1Chr21:24\">1CH 21:23–21:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:10-Jer32:12\">JER 32:10–32:12</a></p>\n<h3>They add force to words</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:7\">1SA 11:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:25-Josh7:26\">JOS 7:25–7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:27-1Sam15:28\">1SA 15:27–15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:16\">2SA 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12-Matt21:13\">MAT 21:12–21:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15-Mark11:17\">MRK 11:15–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45-Luke19:46\">LUK 19:45–19:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:15-John2:16\">JHN 2:15–2:16</a> <em>Use of gestures illustrates the demonstrative nature of much communication in the cultures of biblical times.</em></p>\n<h2>Gestures often convey more than words</h2>\n<h3>Gestures of joy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:14\">2SA 6:14</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:6\">GEN 21:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:24\">LEV 9:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:8\">ACT 3:8</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:5\">1SA 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:3\">GEN 37:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:19\">1SA 2:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:46-Luke7:47\">LUK 7:46–7:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:34\">LUK 10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:20\">LUK 15:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:13\">JHN 15:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of mercy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:6-Isa6:7\">ISA 6:6–6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam24:10-1Sam24:11\">1SA 24:10–24:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:1\">2SA 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam9:7\">2SA 9:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:27\">MAT 18:27</a> <em>Mercy itself is a gesture of love.</em></p>\n<h3>Gestures of worship and reverence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:5\">EXO 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:14\">JOS 5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:6\">NEH 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:4\">PSA 63:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps134:2\">PSA 134:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:11\">MAT 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:8\">LUK 5:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:32\">JHN 11:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of repentance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:6\">JOB 42:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:27\">1KI 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:1\">EZR 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa22:12\">ISA 22:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:12\">JOL 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:6-Jonah3:8\">JON 3:6–3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:21\">MAT 11:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:13\">LUK 10:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3-Matt27:5\">MAT 27:3–27:5</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of sorrow and mourning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:31\">2SA 3:31</a></strong> <em>Gestures of sorrow and mourning are very similar to those of repentance and remorse.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:4\">2SA 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth4:1\">EST 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps137:1\">PSA 137:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:13\">JOL 1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:16\">AMO 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of dedication</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10\">GEN 17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod21:6\">EXO 21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:41-1Sam20:42\">1SA 20:41–20:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:35-Neh10:37\">NEH 10:35–10:37</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of anger</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:28\">LUK 15:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:19\">EXO 32:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:27\">NUM 22:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:33-1Sam20:34\">1SA 20:33–20:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:65\">MAT 26:65</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:63\">MRK 14:63</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:54\">ACT 7:54</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:57\">ACT 7:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:16\">REV 3:16</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of treachery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:47-Luke22:48\">LUK 22:47–22:48</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:47-Matt26:49\">MAT 26:47–26:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:43-Mark14:45\">MRK 14:43–14:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:27\">2SA 3:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam20:9-2Sam20:10\">2SA 20:9–20:10</a></p>\n<h3>Gestures of contempt</h3>\n<p>Shaking of the head:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:7\">PSA 22:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:8\">PSA 64:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39\">MAT 27:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:29\">MRK 15:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:67\">MAT 26:67</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:65\">MRK 14:65</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:16\">REV 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>Other examples of gestures</h2>\n<h3>The gesture of washing hands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:24\">MAT 27:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:6-Deut21:7\">DEU 21:6–21:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:6\">PSA 26:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:13\">PSA 73:13</a></p>\n<h3>The gesture of shaking dust from the feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:14\">MAT 10:14</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:11\">MRK 6:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:5\">LUK 9:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:11\">LUK 10:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:51\">ACT 13:51</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's gesture of washing the disciples' feet</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:4-John13:5\">JHN 13:4–13:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:12-John13:15\">JHN 13:12–13:15</a> <em>This was a gesture of service and a lesson in both serving and being willing to accept service.</em></p>",
